FBIS3-33202 "drlat035_c_94011" FBIS-LAT-94-035 Document Type:Daily Report 22 Feb 1994 MEXICO Late Start for Official Talks PA2102191194 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 1803 GMT 21 Feb 94 PA2102191194 Mexico City NOTIMEX Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] San Cristobal de las Casas, 21 Feb (Notimex) -- The dialogue between Manuel Camacho Solis, peace commissioner for the southeastern State of Chiapas, and 19 delegates from the Zapatist National Liberation Army began here today two hours late. The parties began the official talks in private at 1100 (1700 GMT) at the San Cristobal cathedral under strict security measures and with the mediation of Bishop Samuel Ruiz, according to a spokesman for the bishop. Francisco Hernandez, spokesman for the diocese, added that a news conference will be held at 1800 (0000 GMT) at the cathedral, which is being guarded by military police, nongovernment organizations, as well as the Mexican and international Red Cross.
